Description: Jaipur is a card game for two players. 
    It was created by SÃ©bastien Pauchon in 2009 and published by Asmodee.
    Players assume the roles of merchants in Jaipur, the capital of Rajasthan.
    The aim is to receive two "seals of excellence" and be invited to the court of the Maharaja. 
